{%- comment -%}
  Back to top (spec §5.5: "44px circle, Surface + shadow-md, thin up arrow;
  appears after 2 viewports, bottom-right, above mobile sticky bars"). The
  "above mobile sticky bars" part means coordinating with .sticky-atc
  (Milestone 7's mobile add-to-cart bar) — handled entirely in CSS via the
  same breakpoint that bar already hides at, not a JS position calculation.
{%- endcomment -%}
<button type="button" class="back-to-top" data-back-to-top hidden aria-label="{{ 'general.back_to_top' | t }}">
  {% render 'icon', name: 'chevron-down', size: 20, class: 'icon--rotate-180' %}
</button>
